### Tamper-Evident Append-Only Log Service - API Client
# Use the VS Code "REST Client" extension to run these requests directly inside your editor.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiKey = dev-api-key-change-in-production

### 1. Health Check (No Auth Required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Create Log Entry (Valid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/log
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "actor": "alice",
  "action": "document.create",
  "payload": {
    "documentId": "doc_xyz123",
    "title": "Annual Strategy Report",
    "confidential": true
  }
}

###

### 3. Create Log Entry (Invalid - Missing Fields for Zod Validation Check)
POST {{baseUrl}}/log
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "actor": "",
  "payload": {}
}

###

### 4. Create Log Entry (Invalid - Unauthorized Key Check)
POST {{baseUrl}}/log
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: WRONG_KEY_HERE

{
  "actor": "malicious",
  "action": "bypass.auth",
  "payload": {}
}

###

### 5. Get Log Entry By ID
# Change ID to an entry that exists in your SQLite database
GET {{baseUrl}}/log/1
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Verify Entire Hash Chain Integrity
GET {{baseUrl}}/verify
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 7. Export Logs (All entries - Unfiltered)
GET {{baseUrl}}/export
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 8. Export Logs (Filtered by Actor & Date Range)
# Note: Dates must be ISO-8601 compliant
GET {{baseUrl}}/export?actor=alice&startDate=2026-05-21T00:00:00.000Z
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json
